# Scanner image .trivyignore — explicit CVE allowlist with rationale.
#
# Format: CVE-XXXX-NNNNN<TAB># reason
#
# Listed CVEs come from the debian:12-slim base layer (perl-base) and have
# no upstream fix available (fix_deferred per the Debian security tracker).
# The scanner binary itself does not invoke perl; the package is a transitive
# Debian dep brought in by `coreutils`. Removing perl-base would require
# rebuilding on a leaner base image — tracked separately under REM-014
# follow-up (Debian-slim → distroless audit). Until then, ignore the
# specific CVEs so trivy still gates against new findings.

CVE-2026-42496
